author: Jacob Davey
title: Could the #LilUziVertChallenge Land Lil Uzi Vert a No.1?
text:
Lil Uzi Vert’s Luv Is Rage 1.5 has been getting bumped in the Highsnobiety office an unholy amount since he dropped the 4 tracks on his Soundcloud recently. All the tracks are strong, but it’s the Philly rapper’s twinkling, melancholic “XO Tour Llif3″ which has blown up the most in popularity, gaining nearly 20 million (!) plays already.
The TM88-produced track is now so big it’s spawned it’s own hashtag – #LilUziVertChallenge. Fans of Uzi will know that he’s not afraid to rock some nonchalant dance-moves on camera. If you’re not – check out his voguing below at New York Fashion Week.
@liluzivert #CONTEST Upload your video doing the #liluzivertchallenge For a chance to win a pair of VIP Tickets To see #liluzivert live Friday April 7th @mgmparkbiloxi || Biloxi MS || 7PM Must Tag @springbreakexplosion Must hashtag #SpringBreakExplosion Must hashtag #liluzivertchallenge Winners to be announced every Friday via @instagram 
A post shared by SpringBreakExplosion (@springbreakexplosion) on Mar 10, 2017 at 7:37pm PST 

The challenge has captured the hearts of fans, who are replicating the The Perfect Luv Tape rapper’s increasingly iconic strutting, as you can see below.
#LilUziVertChallenge w/ @meechonmars 
A post shared by Kenny Knox (@kennyjknox) on Mar 7, 2017 at 4:33pm PST 

#LilUziVertChallenge 😂😂 thought I should make a quick vid 🙄🎸🔋® #liluzivert #luvisrage2 #xo 
A post shared by @ren.vlone on Mar 7, 2017 at 10:39am PST 

Check Out My Last Video ASAP! #LilUziVertChallenge •Tag A Friend• 
A post shared by B.A. (@bdotadot5) on Mar 6, 2017 at 9:58pm PST 

#liluzivertchallenge @bdotadot5 
A post shared by @therealjeff__ on Mar 15, 2017 at 2:36pm PDT 

Could this potentially lead the rapper to the number one slot in the charts in a similar fashion to the viral #MannequinChallenege created by Gucci Mane and Rae Sremmund’s “Black Beatles ? At this rate, it could well do. 
Revisit the animated video for “XO Tour Llif3″ below.

In other music news, Tommy Cash is back at it again with the crazy visuals. Check out our premiere of his new track “Surf” here .
